From e9e09b1c15dac506095d21e86d15c52c8375ceff Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sathishkumar Muruganandam <murugana@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 23 Jun 2025 10:55:19 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] UPSTREAM:CP:wifi:ath12k: add WBS support
 for NAC RSSI reporting

WBS (Wide Band Scan) support is required for scan requests for
> 20MHz bandwidth. Existing ROC (remain-on-channel) feature is
extended for this and WMI scan start command appended with WBS
flag for the same.

Remove exiting peer creation for NAC RSSI and replace with new
VDEV_FILTER_NEIGHBOR_RX_PACKETS_CMD for HW AST monitoring.

Add new scan flag WMI_SCAN_FLAG_HIGHER_MCS_NAC_SCAN in start
scan command if there is any NAC client is in monitoring and
WBS request, both in place for enabling higher MCS NAC scan
in HW.

Signed-off-by: Sathishkumar Muruganandam <murugana@qti.qualcomm.com>
